Example: Three cars

Two attributes; Economy and Quality
Consider three choice effects; Attraction, Similarity, and Compromise

MAIN FINDINGS
Similarity Effect
Pr(A|{A,B}) > Pr(B|{A,B})
BUT
Pr(A|{A,B,S}) < Pr(B|{A,B,S})
Attraction Effect
Pr(A|{A,B}) < Pr(B|{A,B})
BUT
Pr(A|{A,B,D}) > Pr(B|{A,B,D})
Compromise Effect
Pr(A|{A,B}) > Pr(B|{A,B})
BUT
Pr(A|{A,B,C}) Pr(B|{A,B,C})
